prev_sentence:
[65 FR 82802, Dec. 28, 2000, as amended at 67 FR 53266, Aug. 14, 2002; 68 FR 8381, Feb. 20, 2003; 74 FR 42769, Aug. 24, 2009;
78 FR 5695, Jan. 25, 2013]
§ 164.502 Uses and disclosures of protected health information: General rules.

next_sentence:
This requirement does not apply to:
(i)
Disclosures to or requests by a health care provider for treatment;
(ii)
Uses or disclosures made to the individual, as permitted under paragraph (a)(1)(i) of this
section or as required by paragraph (a)(2)(i) of this section;
(iii) Uses or disclosures made pursuant to an authorization under § 164.508;
(iv) Disclosures made to the Secretary in accordance with subpart C of part 160 of this subchapter;
(v)
Uses or disclosures that are required by law, as described by § 164.512(a); and
(vi) Uses or disclosures that are required for compliance with applicable requirements of this
subchapter.

